reviews.review_text: Dead in St Louis Mo.USA at this show like most of the other ones twos and threes.Terrific always.Its a theater the sound was sweet !

Why? Sean, can you please tell me what the purpose of track 24 is? 16 seconds at the beginning of TOO. So we get Truckin', interruption, 16 seconds of music, interruption, 3 minutes of drums, interruption, then TOO. Couldn't you have put tracks 24, 25 and 26 together and called them The Other One?

Can anyone explain this to me?

Then you do it again, "China Cat Sunflower Jam", 53 seconds. You've taken a beautiful set they performed and inserted NINE, count 'em, 9 interruptions! Yeesh!

Fox shows These shows are laid back, but are emotionally charged.
Big Railroad, Comes A Time and The Other One are quite enjoyable. 
I do not prefer any other BRB to this one.
